sentences: Bill D'Elia directed the film which was shot in Nashville, TN, between July 11 and August 4, 1994.
The film first aired on January 22, 1995, on CBS.

The movie then moves to the 60s where West skyrockets to fame as a country music singer with the Top 10 hit "Here Comes My Baby Back Again", which then leads to West winning a Grammy Award in 1965, becoming the first female country singer to win a Grammy.
West's family, including her children (William, Shelly, Mo, Dale) helped with the making of the movie.
